cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper deals with the problem of learning to predict the physical dynamics of objects interacting in a visual scene, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper evaluates several state-of-the-art unsupervised deep learning models, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of curriculum-based teaching, which is relevant to the field of robotics (cs.RO).
